        },
        "body": "This issue focuses on improving the robustness and reliability of the pdb_to_seq_uniprot function.\n\nI would like to work on this issue.\n\nProposed Approach\nAdd input validation to ensure pdb_id is a non-empty string\nIntroduce timeout handling for external API requests to prevent indefinite blocking\nWrap API calls in try/except blocks to handle network-related errors gracefully\nAdd checks for missing UniProt mappings to avoid runtime errors\nReplace unsafe FASTA parsing (next()) with a safer parsing approach\nImprove error messages for better clarity and debugging\n\nThe goal is to ensure the function fails gracefully with informative messages instead of crashing in edge cases, while keeping the existing functionality unchanged.\n\nAdditional Note\n\nI noticed that some PDB IDs map to multiple UniProt entries. Currently, the function selects the first UniProt ID. I would like to confirm whether this behavior should be retained or extended to support multiple mappings before implementing further changes.\n\nI’d be happy to proceed based on your guidance. Please let me know if I can be assigned to this issue.",
